&lt;p&gt;Any help would be much appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5930/off-center-text-in-status-bar/?answer=5937#post-id-5937</link><description>The issue seems to be with the font i was using, font awesome. The only reason i was using font awesome was for their icons. You can set up your fonts so that there is a fallback font if the symbols aren't in the first font. So setting font awesome as a fall back font allows you to have an arbitrary font for text and font awesome for icons only.

The following config lines have solved my problem.

     bar {
          font pango: Inconsolata, FontAwesome 10
    }

This will both center the text and display the icons you want.
</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2015 22:41:28 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5930/off-center-text-in-status-bar/?answer=5937#post-id-5937</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Airblader for &lt;p&gt;The issue seems to be with the font i was using, font awesome. The only reason i was using font awesome was for their icons. You can set up your fonts so that there is a fallback font if the symbols aren't in the first font. So setting font awesome as a fall back font allows you to have an arbitrary font for text and font awesome for icons only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following config lines have solved my problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt; bar {
      font pango: Inconsolata, FontAwesome 10
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will both center the text and display the icons you want.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5930/off-center-text-in-status-bar/?comment=5939#comment-5939</link><description>Nevertheless there was a bug in the alignment of the separators which I fixed. So thanks anyway!</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2015 03:47:22 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5930/off-center-text-in-status-bar/?comment=5939#comment-5939</guid></item></channel></rss>